    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinctive censers, suspended by chains, used for rituals and liturgies. A thurible usually comprises a metal receptacle, often with a pierced cover, containing combustible material to burn gums used as incense; swung by hand or hung on a stand.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
